Tool Used: Canva
Infographic File: digital_literacy_infographic.png

I created this digital literacy infographic on Canva to visually break down key concepts for students navigating the digital world.
It covers three main areas — what digital literacy means, essential tools for students like Notion, Google Scholar, and Slack, and safe internet practices 
including strong passwords, two-factor authentication, phishing awareness, and privacy settings. 
The design uses a clean, colour-coded layout with icons to make each section easy to read and engaging.

